<TITLE> Police, magistrates discuss trial jams </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 11 (bdnews24.com)A meeting between police and magistrates in the capital Saturday sought to identify ways to inject pace into the trial process and ensure higher standards of justice. Dhaka district judicial magistrates presented a paper titled 'Existing complications in the investigation and trial of judicial cases and immediate solutions' at the Dhaka district courts Jagannath Sohel auditorium in the city. Problems identified in the paper included a lack of clear information regarding the accused, overlong criminal investigations and reports consistently reaching the court late and containing irregularities. Proper age-identification of minors, time wasting in medical tests for rape cases and irregularities in maintaining criminal case diaries were also raised in the paper. b
